<br />
The only nootropic I've taken to date has been Alertec (Provigil), but I never took it like this guy did; I took it when I had no time to sleep one night. And, yeah, it basically made me feel exactly how I feel after I've had a full night's sleep. Not 'pepped' or 'hyper' like caffeine would, just completely normal - despite having not slept. And nor did it stop me being able to sleep later, either. It's was like the bit of the brain that makes you feel like you want to sleep simply didn't exist (but I still could when I chose to).<br />
